COMBAT: Palladium Rifts combat system

OVERVIEW:
  Combat in AetherMUD is based on the Palladium Rifts RPG system.
  Each character has a set number of Attacks Per Melee (APM) which
  reset every 15 seconds.

STARTING COMBAT:
  kill <target>      - Attack a target and enter combat.

APM (Attacks Per Melee):
  Your APM is based on OCC and Physical Prowess bonus:
    - Peak fighters (Cyber-Knight, Crazy, Juicer, Tattooed Man): 6
    - Assassin / Specialist: 5
    - Military OCC: 4
    - Magic users: 3
    - Civilians: 2
  A high PP stat gives +1 APM (PP 16-19) or +2 APM (PP 20+).

AUTO-PARRY:
  Free. Always active. Uses your parry bonus against incoming attacks.
  Type: autoparry to see your current bonus.

AUTO-DODGE:
  Optional. Costs 1 APM when triggered. Can dodge attacks that parry
  cannot handle. Disable to conserve APM. Type: autododge to toggle.

MDC vs SDC:
  MDC (Mega-Damage Capacity) characters take no damage from SDC weapons.
  MDC weapons drain armor MDC first; damage overflows to body MDC after
  armor is destroyed.
  SDC characters use armor AR rolls to block.

DEATH:
  When HP or MDC falls to 0 you die. A 10-second respawn timer begins.
  You keep your inventory. A credit chip with 10% of your credits drops
  at the death site.

ESCAPE:
  flee    - Run in a random direction. PP-based success, min 30%.
  stop    - Cease your attacks. Passive enemies may stop too.

TATTOO WEAPONS:
  Use 'touch <location> tattoo' to summon tattoo weapons.
  They are MDC and last until their duration expires.

SEE ALSO: flee, stop, autoparry, autododge, touch, equipment
